    Intel® CoreTM 14th Gen i9-14900KS

    The World’s Fastest Desktop Processor1

    Game without compromise. Aimed at extreme gamers and enthusiasts, Intel® CoreTM i9-14900KS Processor pushes the maximum boost clock up to 6.2 GHz. Take advantage of Intel’s performance hybrid architecture designed for optimized performance in all scenarios and supercharge your CPU performance with a powerful suite of tuning and overclocking tools.

    Intel® Thermal Velocity Boost

    Opportunistically increases clock frequency by up to 100MHz; available if the CPU’s within temperature limits (70°C for desktops, 65°C for mobile) and turbo power budget is available.

    Intel® Application Optimization

    Determines and directs application resources in real time. This policy optimizes thread scheduling along with application threading for selected software titles and may improve performance for supported applications.

    Intel® Extreme Tuning Utility with AI Assist

    AI Assist is a preview software feature within Intel® Extreme Tuning Utility (Intel® XTU) that uses an AI (Artificial Intelligence) model to generate a proposed set of values for overclocking a system. It allows for easier overclocking as it characterizes individual system configuration.

    Best-in-class Connectivity with Discrete Intel® Wi-Fi 7 (5 Gig) Support

    Get ready for wired-like experiences with the extreme levels of speed, low latency, and reliability enabled by Intel® Wi-Fi 7.

    Intel 7 Process Technology

    Intel 7 Process uses deep ultraviolet lithography and delivers impressive performance increase per watt.

    PCIe 5.0 and 4.0 Support

    Support for PCIe 5.0 ensures fast access to discrete graphics, storage, and peripheral devices, while support for PCIe 4.0 ensures fast access to storage and peripheral devices.

    DDR5 and DDR4 Support

    DDR5 delivers the latest, industry-leading innovation in memory capabilities for fast speeds, high bandwidth, and enhanced workflow productivity. DDR4 Support ensures continued support of existing memory technology and speeds.

    Core and Memory Overclocking

    When paired with the Intel® Z790 or Z690 chipset, processor P-cores, E-cores, graphics, and memory can be set to run at frequencies above the processor specification resulting in higher performance.

    Notes:

    1. At 6.2 GHz Max Turbo Frequency, Intel® CoreTM 19-14900KS processor is the fastest desktop processor (as of March 2024).
